%section#intro
  .overview-tab
    .container-fluid
      .row
        .col-md-12{style: 'padding: 0'}
          = image_tag 'book_top2.png', class: 'img-responsive'
      .row
        .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
          .row
            .col-md-4.overview-header.text-center
              = image_tag 'logo2.jpg', class: 'img-rounded', alt: 'logo', height: '200'
            .col-md-8.overview-text-new
              %p
                The
                %b DDGLC
                (Database and Dictionary of Greek Loanwords in Coptic) project is hosted by the Egyptological Institute -Georg Steindorff- of the University of Leipzig and
                funded by the Deutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft as a long-term project with a projected lifespan ranging through 2024.
              %p
                The DDGLC project seeks to produce a systematic, comprehensive and detailed lexicographical compilation and
                description of Greek loanwords as attested in the entire Coptic corpus through every dialect, each kind of text,
                and in pre-Coptic Egyptian. The project will thus eventually record 1500 years of contact-induced language change
                of the Egyptian-Coptic language. The results of the project shall be made available in an online database
                and in a printed dictionary.
              %p
                The core tool of the DDGLC project is currently a relational database designed to connect linguistic and
                extra-linguistic data concerning types and tokens of all identifiable Greek loanwords in Coptic.
              .overview-links.text-center
                %a.scroll-button{href: '#lexicon'}
                  %button.btn.btn-default.circular
                    = fa_icon 'angle-double-down', class: 'fa-2x'
                %a{href: '/project/about'}
                  %button.btn.btn-default.circular
                    = fa_icon 'angle-double-right', class: 'fa-2x'
      .row
        .col-md-12{style: 'padding: 0'}
          = image_tag 'book_bottom4.jpg', class: 'img-responsive'


%section#lexicon.overview-section
  .overview-tab
    .container
      .row
        .col-md-4.overview-header
          %h2 Lexicon
      .row
        .col-md-4
        .col-md-8.overview-text-new
          %p
            The lexicon summarizes the morphological and semantic information of the data.
            It is divided into three parts. The first part is the Greek Lemma list, which contains the information
            of the processed donor language lemmas. Currently, there are
            %b= pluralize Lemma.count, 'lemma'
            in the database.
          %p
            The second part is the Coptic Sublemma list with more than
            = succeed '.' do
              %b= pluralize Sublemma.count, 'sublemma'
            Each entry represents the morphological
            and semantic information of a loanword.
          %p
            Eventually, the Coptic Usage is the third part. It contains data about the concrete use cases of a sublemma
            in the texts. Within the database, there are
            = succeed ',' do
              %b= pluralize Usage.count, 'usage'
            i.e. on average
            = pluralize (Usage.count.to_f/ Sublemma.count).round(1), 'usages'
            per sublemma.
          .overview-links.text-center
            -#%a.scroll-button{href: '#intro'}
            -#  %button.btn.btn-default.circular
            -#    = fa_icon 'angle-double-up', class: 'fa-2x'
            -#%a.scroll-button{href: '#attestation'}
            -#  %button.btn.btn-default.circular
            -#    = fa_icon 'angle-double-down', class: 'fa-2x'
            %a{href: '/lexicon/about'}
              %button.btn.btn-default.circular
                = fa_icon 'angle-double-right', class: 'fa-2x'


